API: It stands for Application Programming Interface. It is a way for different
    system and applications to communicate with each other. In this we call, put up a request and get a response
    Request: The application (client) sends a request to the API, asking for data or performing an action.
    Response: The API processes the request and responds with the requested data or a result.
    Types of APIs
Web APIs: Allow applications to interact over the internet, usually using HTTP (e.g., REST, SOAP).
Library APIs: Enable programs to use functions from software libraries.
Operating System APIs: Allow apps to interact with OS services (e.g., Windows API).
Database APIs: Help apps retrieve or modify data stored in databases.